description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Test Analyst (Band 6)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Leeds&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and dynamic individual with a background in software development to join our Test Team. The role of Test Analyst will play an important part in the implementation and continued evolution of an exciting Informatics Strategy underpinned by a largeIT Capital Programme, including the delivery of aTrust-ledElectronic Patient Record System (EHR) development programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals’ Informatics Directorate is committed to supporting its clinical areas through clinically led technology implementations. The EHR programme within the informatics strategy is crucial to the Trust realising its goal of promoting innovation and redesigning services to deliver tailored care. As a Test Analyst, you will be part of a small expert team responsible for testing regular releases of our EHR to help ensure that it meets the vision of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience required for the Test Analyst:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ISTQB Software Testing Foundation Certificate or equivalent recognised testing qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At least two years’ experience in System, Integration Testing and UAT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Risk-based testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hands-on experience of logging, tracking defects from open to close using Test / Defect Management Tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantial demonstrable experience of working with Agile/SCRUM environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to define test conditions and test coverage from requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge and understanding of testing methodologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to work efficiently on multiple work streams within sprints and releases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A strong background in collaborating and communicating with a wide range of technical, clinical staff and stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication and inter personal skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent reporting and analytical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desirable Experience of the Test Analyst:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience using Selenium&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Automation experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of C#&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-browser / cross-platform testing framework.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;API testing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of Jira.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SQL / T-SQL and the ability to join tables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience inperformancetestingtoolsfor troubleshooting and resolvingperformancerelatedissues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding of the NHS and how it exchanges information from one part of the service to another (out of hours, NHS Direct, A&amp;E, GP’s, appointments and data repositories).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding of healthcare specific technologies and solutions (i.e HL7 messaging and Patient Administration System).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust offers a fantastic opportunity for continued professional development and fresh challenges at an enterprise scale as one of the largest NHS trusts in the country. We have an international reputation for excellence in specialist care, research and academic training and this role will help support and sustain our strategy and goal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any queries please contact:- &lt;span&gt;lisaurwin@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
